Description: Fragment of floor and conical foot of East Greek pottery cup;glaze fired red-brown; interior glazed with two added white rings; exterior glazed; underside reserved; inscription on underside.

Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 316)
Johnston 2006a / Trademarks on Greek Vases: Addenda (East Greek 187)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.158)
